        <body>
            <head>Indices</head>
            <p>Indices provide simple access to the information in Hofmeister XIX through
                alphabetical listings, and are a good way of discovering the extent and range of
                what it contains. They are available for Composers, Publishers, Places (i.e. places
                of publication), Class (i.e. Hofmeister classification), and Country (based on 2006
                boundaries). In the case of Place you have the further option of identifying the
                location on a map. All indices make use of <xref type="internal" from="p3_8">thesauri</xref>, the
                purpose of which is to bring together equivalent entries (J. S. Bach, Bach J. S.,
                Sebastian Bach, etc); where, exceptionally, you wish to access information without
                using thesauri, use Search instead.</p>
            <p>Available indices (based on thesauri):</p>
            <list>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="index_composers">Composers</xref>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="index_publishers">Publishers</xref>
                </item>
                <item> Publication places (<xref type="internal" from="index_pubPlaces">list</xref>
                    or <xref type="internal" from="map">map</xref>) </item>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="index_hofclasses">Classes</xref>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="index_countries">Countries</xref>
                </item>
            </list>
        </body>
